Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect, Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect, and Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony are available.

To set up a third-party identity provider solution to log in to Service Cloud Voice, follow these steps:

1. From Setup, enter Contact Centers in the Quick Find box.
2. Select Amazon Contact Centers for Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect or Partner Telephony Contact Centers for Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect and Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony.
3. Click the contact center name for which you want to enable your third-party identity provider.
4. In the contact center details page, configure your identity provider.

Required user permissions:

* Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers
* Contact Center Admin
* Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers
* Contact Center Admin (Partner Telephony)
title: Configuring Third-Party SSO for Service Cloud Voice
